President Jacob Zuma apologised on Tuesday to the ANC s national working committee (NWC) over party officials handling of his cabinet reshuffle, in which former finance minister Pravin Gordhan, his deputy Mcebisi Jonas and three other ministers were axed.The president initially used a questionable intelligence document on a purported plot by Gordhan and Jonas to justify his reshuffle, when a simple explanation would have sufficed.ANC secretary-general Gwede Mantashe said Zuma had removed Gordhan due to irreconcilable differences between the two which was sufficient reason for the president to take the step.There had been no need for Zuma to use the so-called intelligence report to justify his intended actions.If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: President s apology tames detractorsIf you would like to&nbsp;subscribe &nbsp;to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please&nbsp;click here: SubscribePremium content is not yet available on the app. Please use the desktop site to subscribe.